  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Accountant/Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Spearhead and mentor a high-performance finance team, cultivating a culture of continuous professional development, engagement, and operational efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Formulate and execute policies and procedures that align with business objectives while ensuring compliance with regulatory standards and industry best practices.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the financial management and reporting for Singapore operations, ensuring adherence to accounting principles, regulatory requirements, and corporate policies.</li>\n  <li>Lead the budgeting, forecasting, variance analysis, and cash flow management processes to optimize financial resources and enhance overall performance.</li>\n  <li>Conduct routine internal audits to assess internal control effectiveness and identify opportunities for operational improvements.</li>\n  <li>Provide strategic financial guidance to senior leadership and cross-functional teams, driving operational efficiency, cost optimization, and revenue growth.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, or a related field; Chartered Accountant (CA) qualification is highly preferred.</li>\n  <li>At least 10 years of progressive experience in finance leadership roles, including prior experience as a Finance Manager or in a similar capacity.</li>\n  <li>Deep understanding of financial principles, regulations, and industry best practices.</li>\n  <li>Strong financial acumen and analytical skills, with a proven ability to drive financial performance in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to engage, influence, and collaborate with stakeholders at all levels.</li>\n  <li>Proven leadership in building and nurturing high-performing finance teams.</li>\n  <li>Expertise in financial modeling, analysis tools, ERP systems, and advanced Microsoft Excel skills.</li>\n  <li>Strong problem-solving ability, with a talent for interpreting complex financial data and delivering actionable insights.</li>\n  <li>Meticulous attention to detail, ensuring accuracy and integrity in all financial reporting and analysis.</li>\n  <li>Ability to adapt to a fast-changing environment with competing priorities and tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Comprehensive knowledge of regulatory requirements, accounting standards, and tax laws relevant to the semiconductor industry and Singapore.</li>\n  <li>Candidates with GTP and MES expertise are encouraged to apply. Highly experienced candidates may be considered for senior roles with competitive compensation packages.</li>\n</ul>",
